The paper deals with the construction of subspace codes, which are closely related to information theory and coding theory (cs.IT). The authors also mention a connection to the theory of designs over finite fields, which falls under discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The construction method used in the paper involves linear algebra and optimization techniques, which are common in the field of coding theory and communication complexity (cs.CC). The authors also mention the use of numerical algorithms to find the best codes, which falls under numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper discusses the application of subspace codes in network coding, which is a topic in the field of signal processing and information theory (cs.SI).
